                    "id": "n9n0cui",
                    "author": "LordGwyn-n-Tonic",
                    "score": 23,
                    "body": "This is frustrating to read. My grandpa had Alzheimer's but everyone pretended he didn't. He sold his house to a member of his congregation for a third of its market value, kind of on a whim, and later forgot about it. And the courts ruled that because he had signed paperwork, despite clearly not being well, it was binding. And so he lost the house he had built, which was worth over a million, for only 300k.",
