        "score": 4,
        "body": "Anna Nicole Smith died from an accidental overdose of prescription drugs. The combination of [chloral hydrate](https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-1-d&amp;sca_esv=1c2c48b035966a68&amp;channel=entpr&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifNSUXbSYNW4Uy-5MxjFcIFKeXLifg:1755700816866&amp;q=chloral+hydrate&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiksZWcz5mPAxXX6ckDHdBhNTEQxccNegUIhgEQAQ) with other medications, including four [benzodiazepines](https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-1-d&amp;sca_esv=1c2c48b035966a68&amp;channel=entpr&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifNSUXbSYNW4Uy-5MxjFcIFKeXLifg:1755700816866&amp;q=benzodiazepines&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiksZWcz5mPAxXX6ckDHdBhNTEQxccNegUIhgEQAg), was cited as the cause, [according to Wikipedia](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anna_Nicole_Smith). Other drugs found in her system included [diphenhydramine](https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-1-d&amp;sca_esv=1c2c48b035966a68&amp;channel=entpr&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifNSUXbSYNW4Uy-5MxjFcIFKeXLifg:1755700816866&amp;q=diphenhydramine&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiksZWcz5mPAxXX6ckDHdBhNTEQxccNegUIhwEQAQ) and [topiramate](https://www.google.com/search?client=firefox-b-1-d&amp;sca_esv=1c2c48b035966a68&amp;channel=entpr&amp;sxsrf=AE3TifNSUXbSYNW4Uy-5MxjFcIFKeXLifg:1755700816866&amp;q=topiramate&amp;sa=X&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiksZWcz5mPAxXX6ckDHdBhNTEQxccNegUIhwEQAg). She was found unresponsive in a hotel room in Hollywood, Florida, on February 8, 2007",
